<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06163173 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06163173 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  IRAN; FORECAST; IRAQ; ASSAULT; REFUGEE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Iranian radio said today that 100,000 Iraqi troops were preparing an all-outoffensive on hundreds of thousands of Shiite Muslim refugees in the marshlandsof southern Iraq.;    Iran's television Monday reported explosions there andsaid they were the start of an intensive attack on refugees pinned down inmarshes near Iran's border. It also said troops had clashed with civilians intwo southern cities.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  IRAN WARNS OF IRAQ ATTACK ON REFUGEES  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The reports, which followed accounts of persistent hit-and-run operationsby Shiite rebels against government forces in the southern Iraqi city ofBasra, could not be independently confirmed. Iraq on Sunday denied reports itwas planning an offensive and has issued no comment on the reports sincethen.;    State Department spokeswoman Margaret Tutwiler said in WashingtonMonday that there was no evidence of the attack.;    U.N. officials, theoffice of High Commission for Refugees in New York, and the New York office ofthe International Committee of the Red Cross today could not confirm theIranian reports.;    Iranian media have been accurate in reporting internaldevelopments in Iraq in the past few years. Tehran has been hostile towardIraq regarding Baghdad's treatment of the Shiites in southern Iraq.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Nicosia, Cyprus  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910611  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  194  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday June 11, 199100163173,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LAN